# CSS Architecture Rules

## ITCSS Layer Structure
Reference [main.scss](mdc:src/frontend/src/css/main.scss) for import order

### Layer 1: Settings
- Global variables and configuration
- Color system, typography, spacing
- No actual CSS output

### Layer 2: Tools
- Mixins, functions, and utilities
- No actual CSS output

### Layer 3: Generic
- Reset and base styles
- Normalize.css, box-sizing

### Layer 4: Elements
- HTML element styles
- Typography, forms, buttons

### Layer 5: Objects
- Layout and structural styles
- Grid systems, containers

### Layer 6: Components
- UI component styles
- Buttons, cards, modals

### Layer 7: Utilities
- Helper classes
- Spacing, visibility, alignment

## File Naming Convention
- Use underscore prefix: `_settings.scss`, `_buttons.scss`
- Group related styles: `_header.scss`, `_navigation.scss`
- Use semantic names: `_toast.scss`, `_modal.scss`

## Semantic Color Usage
Reference [_settings.scss](mdc:src/frontend/src/css/settings/_settings.scss)

### Primary Colors
```scss
color: var(--color-primary-text);
background: var(--color-surface);
border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
```

### Status Colors
```scss
&.success { color: var(--color-success); }
&.error { color: var(--color-error); }
&.warning { color: var(--color-warning); }
&.info { color: var(--color-info); }
```

### Dark Theme
```scss
[data-theme="dark"] {
  --color-surface: #1a1a1a;
  --color-primary-text: #e2e8f0;
}
